Johannesburg residents were warned to expect possible hail, thunderstorms and downpours in parts of the city late on Thursday afternoon. The SA Weather Service issued a warning, saying that large amounts of small  hail had been observed over the western parts of the city, including Randburg and Sandton. The inclement weather was moving northwards. In a separate warning, the service advised that severe thunderstorms had been observed over the northern parts of the Amajuba district in KwaZulu-Natal with large hail, damaging winds and heavy downpours moving into the south-eastern parts of Mpumalanga.